    "title": "[Mac] Blockchain corrupts on every quit, shows terrible dialog",
    "body": "### Is there an existing issue for this?\n\n- [x] I have searched the existing issues\n\n### Current behaviour\n\n1. I'm loading blockchain, and when quitting Mac app it corrupts every time.\n2. It shows dialog where if I press highlighted button whole blockchain is deleted and it starts downloading again.\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\n1. It does not corrupt ever.\n2. It shows options to fix it without removing. And remove options is not highlighted but is with red color and additional dialog to confiirm, telling that it would remove blockchain.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Start downloading.\n2. Quit the app.\n\n### Relevant log output\n\n<log already overwritten>\n\n### How did you obtain Bitcoin Core\n\nPre-built binaries\n\n### What version of Bitcoin Core are you using?\n\n28.1\n\n### Operating system and version\n\nMacOS 15.3.2 (24D81)\n\n### Machine specifications\n\nMacOS, MacBook M1, external HD ExFAT (Disk Utility First Aid shows everything is OK), good WIFI",
